Date: Wed, 22 Aug 2012 14:32:38 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 56/57] powerpc/t4240: fix the ifc error interrupt

On t4240 all the device's error interrupt are routed to one common
irq. So we also need to set the interrupt type and the bit number of
the error interrupt in the 3rd and 4th cell of the interrupt specifiers.

Signed-off-by: Kevin Hao <kexin.hao@windriver.com>
---
 arch/powerpc/boot/dts/fsl/t4240si-post.dtsi |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/fsl/t4240si-post.dtsi b/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/fsl/t4240si-post.dtsi
index b915387..e461db0 100644
--- a/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/fsl/t4240si-post.dtsi
+++ b/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/fsl/t4240si-post.dtsi
@@ -36,7 +36,7 @@
 	#address-cells = <2>;
 	#size-cells = <1>;
 	compatible = "fsl,ifc", "simple-bus";
-	interrupts = <16 2 0 0 25 2 0 0>;
+	interrupts = <16 2 1 19 25 2 0 0>;
 };
 
 &bportals {
